=== Project Name : <Learn Web/>
=== Technology used  == Html, Css and Javascript


Path
asset folder - Css folder
             - js folder
             - img folder

Content
Css folder - custom stylesheet is located here...
js folder - custom javascript file is located here...
img folder - it houses all image on the site

====================================================================================
================  ⚠⚠⚠  NOTE!!! ⚠⚠⚠⚠ ============================================

==> You are not permitted to alter any existing codes [css and js file]
==> Read and follow the guideline carefully



===== GUIDELINES TO FOLLOW ========
==> You are to build your custom profile card at the student-profile-card-section

==> create your profile card inside this section
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    <div class="student-profile-card">

    </div>
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------

==> your profile card must follow this procedures  (nb: you can copy and paste if you want)

---> Create a profile-card div with another class of your firstname
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    <div class="profile-card your-first-name">
    ...
    </div>

... You can give it another background of your choice in the css file:
---------------------------------------------
.your-first-name{
    background-color: purple !important;
}
---------------------------------------------
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------

---> create an img element with your image in the src attribute add another class of 'my-image-your-first-name'
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
<img src="./asset/img/your image name.extention of the image(jpg,png...)" alt="" class="image-top my-image-your-first-name">
(nb: do not erase the image-top class)

... You can style your image any design that you like and it must be on hover:
----------------------------------------------------------------
.my-image-your-first-name:hover{
    opacity:0.2; - you can add any styling that you like here
}
----------------------------------------------------------------
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------

--> create a span with a class of 's-name' add another class of 's-your-first-name'
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------     
    <span class="s-name s-your-first-name">
        Surname Name .O  (and middle name as initials)
    </span>     
(nb: you will later reference this class in the js file) 
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 

--> create another span with a class of 's-stack'
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
    <span class="s-stack">
        Frontend  - your stack in between (either frontend or backend)
    </span>
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 

--> create a button with a class of 'profile-btn'
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
    <button class="profile-btn">My profile</button>
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 


---> And finally your profile-card must look like this look like this
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------             
    <div class="profile-card">
        <img src="./asset/img/log.jpg" alt="" class="image-top">
             <span class="s-name">
                    Template Name .O
            </span>
            <span class="s-stack">
                    Frontend
            </span>
    <button class="profile-btn">My profile</button>
    </div>
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 


--> Create a new function in the javascript file

==> 1. create a var name of Your First Name
----------------------------------------------------------------------
var YourFirstName = document.querySelector('.s-your-first-name')
----------------------------------------------------------------------

==> 2. create a function to alert your name
----------------------------------------------------------------------
function alertYourFirstName()
{
    alert(YourFirstName.innerHTML);
}
---------------------------------------------------------------------